cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CR, cs.MM

This paper involves deep learning approaches for image classification, specifically for chest X-ray images. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the performance of two state-of-the-art classification deep networks, which falls under the category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). The use of adversarial attacks and modification of pooling operations also suggests the possibility of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) categories. Finally, the specific task of chest X-ray classification may also relate to cs.MM (Multimedia).
